==In education==
Cornell University offers a National Institutes of Health (NIH) funded program through the Science Education Partnership Award (SEPA) Program called Advancing Secondary Science Education thru Tetrahymena (ASSET). The group develops stand-alone labs or lessons using Tetrahymena as training modules that teachers can use in classes.

